Comment:
I like to know who was the person who dropped the screenplay of this movie (now considered one of the worst movies of the 2010's) off at Blake Lively‚Äôs doorstep...because that person made the worst mistake of their life (just as the person who dropped off the script of ‚ÄúDaredevil‚Äù for Jennifer Garner). 
The individual should of had delivered the script to ‚ÄúCrazy Stupid Love‚Äù instead (and in return given the script of ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù to Emma Stone; can you believe she co-stared with Reynolds in "Paperman"?), because Lively does not fit in as Carol, and with ‚ÄúCrazy Stupid Love‚Äù it would of not only re-team Blake Lively with Julianne Moore (they were in ‚ÄúThe Private Lives of Pippa Lee‚Äù) but come face to face that with the person that I feel would had tamed and loved Lively a lot more: Ryan Gosling* (I have a feeling he and Jason Lee are Reynolds).
This is nothing new: Several years ago, my sister Ashley (who has the same crazy-like-a-fox mentality as Lively) was in a relationship with a dark haired guy named Kyle and my Mom (who had kicked her out of her house a few years prior), liked him and thought my sister had turned a new leaf. Well, you can guess what happened: She broke up with him after a while and even today, my mother still believes he was the person my sister could of married.
Well, there you go: The ultimate ‚ÄòWhat If‚Äô do-over in the corrupt, nasty playground known as Hollywood (or is ‚ÄúHow Weird‚Äù?).

*this is what actually did happen to actor (and former football player) Glenn Cadrez when he met Brande Roderick for the horror movie ‚ÄúHood of Horror‚Äù (she was like a wildcat when it came to her beauty)
